|CKBStreet Samurai Cortex Fabrication|000

|CKBLocation and access|000
|CK0The Cortex Fabrication Bay is east of Rin Kade's private ripperdoc clinic.
Only registered Street Samurai may enter or operate its fabrication table.
Builders may enter for administration, but fabrication still requires an active
Street Samurai contract.|000

|CKBCybernetics|000
|CK0Salvaging and fabrication use the Cybernetics profession, with normal
profession progression from 0 to 1000. Salvaging lower-grade hardware stops
improving Cybernetics earlier than salvaging advanced hardware. Fabrication
blueprints also have skill and Street Samurai guild-level requirements.|000

|CKBSalvage|000
|CK0Only extracted cyberware directly in your inventory may be salvaged.
Installed, equipped, unique, temporary, auto-loaded, contract-bound, and
explicitly protected hardware is rejected. Salvaging is permanent.|000

|CK0Use:
  salvage <hardware>
  salvage <hardware> confirm

The first command previews and reserves the exact component yield for sixty
seconds. The confirmation destroys that same hardware only after all recovered
components can be deposited. Use reagents cyber or fabricate materials to see
your persistent component balances.|000

|CKBFabrication|000
|CK0Use:
  fabricate list
  fabricate inspect <recipe>
  fabricate <recipe>

The initial blueprints create field and reinforced hardware repair kits. A
failed blueprint or material transaction consumes nothing.|000

|CKBField repair|000
|CK0Carry a fabricated kit and use repairkit <process_id>. Process IDs match
dashboard and logs, such as cortex_os or targeting_suite. A field kit repairs
15 integrity and a reinforced kit repairs 30. Kits work on one installed Street
Samurai process, cannot be used during combat, never exceed 100 integrity, and
are consumed only after a successful repair. They do not clear fragmentation,
patches, ICE, runtime faults, or Heat.|000
